# `@afenda/ui-system` — flat barrel only

**Authority:** [ADR-010](../../docs/architecture/adr/ADR-010-afenda-ui-system-flat-barrel.md) · [ARCH-024 § `@afenda/ui-system`](../../docs/architecture/ARCH-024-package-boundaries.md#afendaui-system) · [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md)

The retired `@afenda/ui` playground gateway, `packages/design-system`, and UI-pipeline skills (`afenda-elite-design-system`, `afenda-elite-ui-handoff`, `admincn-customization`) are **gone** — do not restore them.

## Public import surface (binding)

| Allowed | Forbidden |
|---------|-----------|
| `import { … } from "@afenda/ui-system"` | `from "@afenda/ui"` or any `@afenda/ui/` subpath |
| `import "@afenda/ui-system/styles.css"` in `apps/web/globals.css` | Deep imports (`@afenda/ui-system/components/…`, package-internal paths) |
| `cn` from the barrel | Handrolled primitives under `apps/web/components/ui/**` |

## Adding or regenerating primitives

1. Run `shadcn add <name>` inside `packages/surfaces/ui-system` (style **new-york**, Radix / unified `radix-ui`, lucide only).
2. `components.json` must have **no `registries` key** — built-in shadcn items only.
3. Convert generated `@/` or `#` aliases to **relative** imports inside the package.
4. Export the primitive from `packages/surfaces/ui-system/src/index.ts` (flat barrel).
5. Keep guardrail tests green: `pnpm --filter @afenda/ui-system test` · `pnpm --filter @afenda/web test`.

## Styling

- **Semantic color tokens** live in `packages/surfaces/ui-system/src/styles/tokens.css` — use `bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, etc.
- **Tailwind compilation** is owned by `apps/web/globals.css` (`@import "tailwindcss"`, `tw-animate-css`, `@source` for the package).
- Do not add raw color literals (`#…`, `rgb(…)`, `hsl(…)`) in component source outside the token file.
- Tailwind theme-scale utilities for spacing/dimensions (`h-9`, `px-3`, `gap-2`) are allowed.
- **CSS custom properties on utilities** — binding write lock lives in [afenda-elite-ui-compose](../skills/afenda-elite-ui-compose/SKILL.md) (Locked design hierarchy: `utility-(--token)`, not `utility-[var(--token)]` for new writes). Do not duplicate that table here.

## Visual lock (consistency)

Product UI must **match** Afenda tokens and type/spacing tables — not freestyle aesthetics. Locked hierarchy and QUALITY ORDER (AUTHORITY → CONSISTENCY → CORRECT-COMPONENT → SUITABILITY → SCALABILITY → STABILITY; prettier that breaks a higher rule = failed; no local compensation for missing reusable barrel capability — see SCALABILITY-FIRST / hard rule 15) live in [`.cursor/skills/afenda-elite-ui-compose/SKILL.md`](../skills/afenda-elite-ui-compose/SKILL.md); this rule does not duplicate those numbers.

**Done means gates + suitability + scalability + stability evidence:** apply the ui-compose **capability check** (SCALABILITY-FIRST / hard rule 15 / `UI-CAP-*`) then the **stability verification matrix** for the changed layer(s). Usual floor: `pnpm check:ui-system` (compose-redflags F*, compose-suitability C1–C3, package/web tests, `tailwind-emit` as scoped). `pnpm --filter @afenda/web build` only when the matrix requires it (RSC boundary, structural package change, global CSS/font map, clear Next emit risk). No silent barrel API change (hard rule 12 in ui-compose): additive → tests; rename/removal/default/semantic → same-change consumer migration. No local compensation for missing reusable barrel capability. Recipes are defaults (workflow may justify Dialog/page over Sheet). DataTable stays generic (feature owns fetch/URL/permissions/domain). Ban vague barrel names (Panel/Container/Box/Item/Wrapper/View). Advisory greps are not enough. Full checklist: [afenda-elite-ui-compose](../skills/afenda-elite-ui-compose/SKILL.md). Gate tables (F*/C*) + UI-CAP: [reference.md](../skills/afenda-elite-ui-compose/reference.md).

## RSC boundary

- Root `src/index.ts` carries **no** `"use client"`.
- Interactive primitives keep `"use client"` in their own files (preserved across barrel re-export).
- Server-safe leaves today: `alert`, `badge`, `breadcrumb`, `button`, `button-group`, `card`, `input`, `kbd`, `native-select`, `pagination`, `skeleton`, `textarea` — every other `components/ui/*` must declare `"use client"` (`packages/surfaces/ui-system/__tests__/rsc-boundary.test.ts`).

## Dependencies

- Do not add external/paid shadcn registries, Studio registry keys, or alternate icon packages to the monorepo for product UI.
- Do not introduce parallel UI packages or gateway subpaths.
